Subject: [PATCH 1/7] cert-hyp: Add kernel option for certifiable hypervisor

Certifiable hypervisor comes with non-debug and debug version,
kernel options CONFIG_WRHV_CERT is needed. For debug version,
User need to pass boot args "cert_debug" via BootLine. Debug
version of hypervisor has additional debug show avaiable
to guest OS.

example BootLine="console=ttyS0,9600 rw root=/dev/ram cert_debug"

Signed-off-by: Thomas Tai <thomas.tai@windriver.com>
---
 init/Kconfig.wrhv |    8 ++++++++
 1 files changed, 8 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/init/Kconfig.wrhv b/init/Kconfig.wrhv
index 792c2a0..0fef307 100644
--- a/init/Kconfig.wrhv
+++ b/init/Kconfig.wrhv
@@ -8,6 +8,14 @@ config WRHV
 	select SERIAL_CORE
 	select SERIAL_CORE_CONSOLE
 
+config WRHV_CERT
+	bool "Certifiable Hypervisor"
+	default n
+	depends on WRHV
+	help
+	  This options select certifiable hypervisor virtualization extensions
+	  in the Linux Kernel
+
 config DEBUG_VIRTUAL_IRQS
 	bool "Debug VIOAPIC with software IRQ"
 	default n
